{"post_stream":{"posts":[{"id":36909,"name":"","username":"Lys0gen","avatar_template":"https://avatars.discourse-cdn.com/v4/letter/l/57b2e6/{size}.png","created_at":"2020-03-22T16:38:27.299Z","cooked":"\u003cp\u003eHello everyone,\u003cbr\u003e\nI am currently having issues with raycasting on a CustomGeometry (TRIANGLE_STRIP). For some reason the hits do detect, but only on the first defined tri. The geometry displays fine and on previous tryouts the raycast worked perfectly on a Terrain, but I don‚Äôt see what I can change here to make it work as expected.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eThe geometry is defined like this:\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cpre\u003e\u003ccode\u003e    CustomGeometry* slopeGeometry = visual-\u0026gt;CreateComponent\u0026lt;CustomGeometry\u0026gt;();\n    slopeGeometry-\u0026gt;BeginGeometry(0, TRIANGLE_STRIP);\n    slopeGeometry-\u0026gt;DefineVertex(verts[0]);\n    slopeGeometry-\u0026gt;DefineTexCoord(tex[0]);\n    slopeGeometry-\u0026gt;DefineNormal(norms[0]);\n\n    slopeGeometry-\u0026gt;DefineVertex(verts[1]);\n    slopeGeometry-\u0026gt;DefineTexCoord(tex[1]);\n    slopeGeometry-\u0026gt;DefineNormal(norms[1]);\n\n    slopeGeometry-\u0026gt;DefineVertex(verts[2]);\n    slopeGeometry-\u0026gt;DefineTexCoord(tex[2]);\n    slopeGeometry-\u0026gt;DefineNormal(norms[2]);\n    [^ tri defined by the above registers with the raycast, any more do not]\n    slopeGeometry-\u0026gt;DefineVertex(verts[3]);\n    slopeGeometry-\u0026gt;DefineTexCoord(tex[3]);\n    slopeGeometry-\u0026gt;DefineNormal(norms[3]);\n    [... potentially more vertices defined here...]\n    slopeGeometry-\u0026gt;Commit();\n\u003c/code\u003e\u003c/pre\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eAnd this is the raycast:\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cpre\u003e\u003ccode\u003eunsigned int MASK = -1;//0xFFFFFFFF\nUrho3D::Ray ray = camera-\u0026gt;GetScreenRay(input-\u0026gt;GetMousePosition().x_/float(getWindow()-\u0026gt;GetSize().x_), input-\u0026gt;GetMousePosition().y_/float(getWindow()-\u0026gt;GetSize().y_));\n\nPODVector\u0026lt;RayQueryResult\u0026gt; result;\nRayOctreeQuery q(result, ray, RAY_TRIANGLE, M_INFINITY, DRAWABLE_GEOMETRY, MASK);\noctree-\u0026gt;RaycastSingle(q);\n\nif(result.Size() \u0026gt; 0){\n[... hit evaluation...]\n\u003c/code\u003e\u003c/pre\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eAdding additional CustomGeometry components to the node makes them register the raycast as well - but again only on the first tri. I guess I could add a new component for every single tri but that seems like a waste.\u003cbr\u003e\nThanks for any help!\u003c/p\u003e","post_number":1,"post_type":1,"updated_at":"2020-03-22T16:40:25.618Z","reply_count":0,"reply_to_post_number":null,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":19,"reads":39,"readers_count":38,"score":102.8,"yours":false,"topic_id":6011,"topic_slug":"raycasting-a-customgeometry-triangle-strip","display_username":"","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"version":1,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_wiki":false,"read":true,"user_title":null,"bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[],"moderator":false,"admin":false,"staff":false,"user_id":1317,"hidden":false,"trust_level":2,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":false},{"id":36910,"name":"","username":"Lys0gen","avatar_template":"https://avatars.discourse-cdn.com/v4/letter/l/57b2e6/{size}.png","created_at":"2020-03-22T18:03:49.626Z","cooked":"\u003cp\u003eOkay sorry, fiddled a bit more with it. The solution is to change the RAY_TRIANGLE parameter of the RayOctreeQuery to either RAY_AABB or RAY_OBB.\u003cbr\u003e\nWhy, I don‚Äôt quite know though.\u003c/p\u003e","post_number":2,"post_type":1,"updated_at":"2020-03-22T18:16:40.625Z","reply_count":0,"reply_to_post_number":null,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":0,"reads":36,"readers_count":35,"score":7.2,"yours":false,"topic_i